In airplane mode a cell phone neither receives nor sends radio signals or data via its antenna, and is thus disconnected from its cellular network and no longer functions as a wireless device.  This forestalls any interference with avionics and permits the use of the phone's internal functions (such as games) as a stand-alone electronic device. 

